sections.heading: corporations; license; required
sections.text: A nonprofit corporation shall not engage in the sale of alcoholic liquor without first having obtained a license required by the Nebraska Liquor Control Act.SourceLaws 1963, c. 310, ยง 11, p. 934;Laws 1965, c. 318, ยง 8, p. 898;Laws 1983, LB 213, ยง 17;Laws 2004, LB 485,
